Newcastle disease, Czech Republic
-------------------------------------------
Information received on 15 Jan 2013 from Dr Milan Malena, Chief Veterinary Officer, Chief Veterinary Officer, Ministry of Agriculture, Prague, Czech Republic

Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 11 Jan 2013
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 11 Jan 2013
Report date: 15 Jan 2013
Date submitted to OIE: 15 Jan 2013
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: Avian paramyxovirus 1
Nature of diagnosis: Clinical, Laboratory (basic), Laboratory (advanced), Necropsy
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks (1)
Outbreak 1: Ivan na Hane, Prostejov, Olomoucky
Date of start of the outbreak: 11 Jan 2013
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Affected animals
Species/ Susceptible/ Cases/ Deaths/ Destroyed/ Slaughtered
Birds/ 46/ 24/ 24/ 22/ 0

Affected population: Backyard pigeons

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Total animals affected
Species/ Susceptible/ Cases/ Deaths/ Destroyed/ Slaughtered
Birds/ 46/ 24/ 24/ 22/ 0

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Unknown or inconclusive

Epidemiological comments: All susceptible birds in the holding were killed and destroyed on 11 Jan 2013. Final cleaning and disinfection will be applied according to legislative measures.

Control measures
Measures applied: Stamping out, Quarantine, Zoning, No vaccination, No treatment of affected animals

Measures to be applied: Disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s)

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: State Veterinary Institute (SVI), Prague (Regional Reference Laboratory)
Species/ Test/ Test date/ Result
Birds/ real-time PCR/ 11 Jan 2013/ Positive

